Czech Stocks: Erste Bank, Komercni Banka, NWR Shares Are Active

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-09-27T10:22:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/czech-stocks-erste-bank-komercni-banka-nwr-shares-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock index
rose 4.5 percent to 942.5 by 12:15 p.m. in Prague, adding to a
4.4 percent advance yesterday.  The following are among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   of  Austria  surged 13 percent
to 514 koruna, heading for its best day in 16 months.  Komercni
Banka AS (KOMB)  , the Czech unit of Societe Generale SA,
jumped 4.7 percent to 3,340 koruna, after rising 6.7 percent
yesterday. Banks led European stocks higher as policy makers
increased efforts to contain the region’s sovereign-debt crisis.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP), the largest Czech coking-
coal producer, jumped 6.5 percent to 141.8 koruna, heading for
its biggest one-day rally in six weeks. Commodities rose for a
second day, with  Europe ’s benchmark coal derivatives climbing to
$123 a metric ton in the Netherlands.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  